Edition:
Quote: <i> Yellow-tail</i>, ... The name is given in Victoria to the fish <i> Caranx trachurus</i>, Cuv. and Val.; the <i> Horse-Mackerel</i> (q.v.) of England. In New South Wales, it is <i> Trachurus declivis</i>, a slightly different species, also called <i> Scad</i>; but the two fish are perhaps the same. . . . Scraenidae in New Zealand, the word is used for the fish <i> Latris lineata</i>, of the family of Sciaenidae, and is also a name for the <i> King-fish, Seriola lalandii</i>, and for the <i> Trevally</i>.
