Date: 0/0/1970
Source: Nomenclature of NZ Fish
Author: SORENSEON
Vol / Page: 31
Edition:
Quote: <i> KINGFISH, NORTHERN</i> (a) Scientific name: <i> Seriola grandis</i>. (b) Suggested commercial name[s]: Kingfish; Yellowtail. (c) Other common names: None known. (d) Principal localities where taken: Auckland, Tauranga, Gisborne, Napier. ...Under the general heading of Kingfish ... is generally lumped with the Silver or Southern Kingfish. <i> Rexea solandri [=<i> Jordanidia solandri</i>] to which it is not related. This fish is a well known gamefish of northern waters.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Fisherman's Bible
Author: WILSON
Vol / Page: 290
Edition:
Quote: YELLOWTAIL The name given overseas, (and in the famous annual Bay of Islands international fishing contest), to our Northern Kingfish (<i> Seriola grandis</i>). Not applied to the Southern Kingfish (<i> Jordanidia solandri</i>) however, who is our sometime Hake of South Island waters. See Kingfish. `Yellowtail' is also a common name given to the Koheru in the north.
